    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat and once hot, add your <strong>ground coriander </strong>and <strong>cumin seeds</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>creamy single soy </strong>gradually to the roux with your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until slightly thickened – this is your <strong>spiced cream</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
